article.description: Guard Allie Quigley scored 23 points to lead DePaul to a 91-56 win over Chicago State.
article.headline: Quigley's 23 points spark DePaul's rout of Chicago State
article.linkText: Quigley sparks DePaul's rout of Chicago State
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Guard Allie Quigley scored 23 points to lead No. 16 DePaul to a 91-56 win over Chicago State on Wednesday.

Guard Dierdre Naughton added 16 points. Erin Carney scored 12 points and was the only other Blue Demon in double figures. Natasha Williams added nine points and 10 rebounds for DePaul.

DePaul (8-0) took a 50-21 lead at the half behind 55.3 percent shooting from the floor.

Chicago State (4-4) was led by guard Jasmin Dixon with 20 points and a game-high 12 rebounds. The only other Cougar in double figures was guard Alyssa Waldon with 11 points.

DePaul scored 31 points off turnovers, while Chicago State managed only 12.
